      <p>Throughout the span of his 27-year career, board-certified plastic surgeon William J. Vasileff, M.D., has achieved a reputation among his patients and peers as a physician whose extensive training and experience in both cosmetic and reconstructive procedures has transformed the way his patients feel about inner and outer beauty.</p>
      <p>A lifelong area resident, Dr. Vasileff's journey in the medical field began in 1974 when he graduated from the <a href="http://www.med.umich.edu/medschool" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;">University of Michigan Medical School</a>. During the next five years, Dr. Vasileff completed his surgical training at <a href="http://www.medschool.northwestern.edu">Northwestern University Medical School</a> in Chicago where he specialized in both General and Ear, Nose and Throat Surgery. After successfully completing his residency in Plastic Surgery at the <a href="http://my.clevelandclinic.org" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;">Cleveland Clinic</a> in Cleveland, Ohio, Dr. Vasileff moved to Philadelphia to undergo a Fellowship in Craniofacial Surgery at the University of Pennsylvania Medical School.</p>
      <p>His specialized and well-rounded training, coupled with a caring nature and expert knowledge, has made Dr. Vasileff a favorite referral of fellow physicians and nurses in the community.</p>
      <p>An active member of the <a href="http://www.ama-assn.org" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;">American Medical Association</a>, as well as the <a href="http://www.msms.org" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;">Michigan</a> and <a href="http://www.ocms-mi.org" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false;">Oakland County</a> Medical Societies, Dr. Vasileff also lectures in the community on various topics relating to plastic surgery.</p>
